<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="84" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/3058</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-06">May 6, 1931</date>.<lb/>[Received May
                                8.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 680</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the
                            President yesterday signed decrees restoring the suspended
                            constitutional guarantees in the provinces of Santa Clara and
                            Camaguey.</p>
                        <pb facs="0180" n="60" xml:id="pg_60"/>
                        <p>Constitutional guarantees thus remain suspended only in the province of
                            Habana, as they were restored in Oriente, Pinar del Rio and Matanzas on
                            April 20.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Edward L. Reed</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>